    <div class="hero">
        <h1>Student Health & Wellness</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="content-container">
        <!-- Introduction Section -->
        <div class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <span class="section-icon">❓</span>
                <h2>Why Student Health Matters-</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="section-content"><img draggable="FLASE" src="/assets/r2.png" class="r2">
                <p>Student life is a unique period filled with academic challenges, social transitions, and personal
                    growth. During this critical phase, maintaining both physical and mental health is essential for
                    academic success and overall well-being. <br><br>
                    Research shows that students who prioritize their health perform better academically, build stronger
                    relationships, and develop lifelong healthy habits. However, many students face significant health
                    challenges due to stress, irregular schedules, poor nutrition, and limited physical activity.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <div class="section-header">

                <h2>Student Health Challenges</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>Research shows that many students face significant health challenges during their academic journey,
                    including stress, anxiety, sleep deprivation, and irregular eating habits. These challenges can
                    impact both academic performance and overall well-being.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Physical Health Section -->
        <div class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <span class="section-icon">💪</span>
                <h2>Physical Health for Students</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>Physical health forms the foundation of a student's ability to learn, focus, and thrive. Poor
                    physical health can lead to decreased energy, concentration problems, and increased susceptibility
                    to illness.</p>

                <h3 style="color: #667eea; margin: 25px 0 15px 0; font-size: 1.4em;">Common Physical Health Challenges:
                </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Poor Nutrition:</strong> Reliance on fast food, skipping meals, and irregular eating
                        patterns can lead to nutrient deficiencies and energy crashes.</li>
                    <li><strong>Sedentary Lifestyle:</strong> Long hours of sitting in classes and studying can
                        contribute to weight gain, poor posture, and cardiovascular issues.</li>
                    <li><strong>Stress-Related Illness:</strong> Chronic stress weakens the immune system, making
                        students more vulnerable to colds, flu, and other infections.</li>
                    <li><strong>Sleep Deprivation:</strong> Late-night studying, social activities, and screen time
                        often result in inadequate sleep, affecting memory, mood, and immune function.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 style="color: #667eea; margin: 25px 0 15px 0; font-size: 1.4em;">Key Physical Health Tips:</h3>
                <div class="tips-grid">
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>😴 Prioritize Sleep</h3>
                        <p>Aim for 7-9 hours of quality sleep. Maintain a consistent sleep schedule and practice sleep
                            hygiene.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>🥗 Eat Balanced Meals</h3>
                        <p>Include fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and proteins. Stay hydrated and limit caffeine and
                            sugar intake.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>🏃 Stay Active</h3>
                        <p>Exercise for at least 30 minutes daily. Take study breaks to stretch and walk around campus.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>🩺 Regular Check-ups</h3>
                        <p>Visit campus health services for routine check-ups and don't ignore persistent symptoms.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>💧 Stay Hydrated</h3>
                        <p>Drink 8-10 glasses of water daily. Carry a reusable water bottle to classes and study
                            sessions.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>🧼 Practice Hygiene</h3>
                        <p>Wash hands regularly, especially during flu season. Maintain good personal hygiene habits.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Mental Health Section -->
        <div class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <span class="section-icon">🧠</span>
                <h2>Mental Health for Students</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>Mental health is just as important as physical health. Students face mental health challenges
                    including academic pressure, personal stress, social isolation, and uncertainty about the future.
                </p>

                <h3 style="color: #667eea; margin: 25px 0 15px 0; font-size: 1.4em;">Common Mental Health Challenges:
                </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Academic Stress:</strong> The pressure to keep up good grades and meet deadlines can
                        cause intense anxiety and lead to burnout.</li>
                    <li><strong>Social Anxiety:</strong> Making new friends, fitting in, and navigating relationships
                        can be emotionally challenging.</li>
                    <li><strong>Depression:</strong> Feelings of sadness, hopelessness, worthlessness, helplessness or
                        loss of interest in
                        activities are common but often go unaddressed.</li>
                    <li><strong>Imposter Syndrome:</strong> Many students feel they don't deserve their achievements or
                        belong in their academic environment.</li>
                    <li><strong>Loneliness:</strong> Being away from family and struggling to build connections can lead
                        to feelings of isolation.</li>
                    <li><strong>Fomo:</strong>Seeing others successes can cause FOMO, making people feel worried and
                        left out.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 style="color: #667eea; margin: 25px 0 15px 0; font-size: 1.4em;">Mental Wellness Strategies:</h3>
                <div class="tips-grid">
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>🗣️ Talk About It</h3>
                        <p>Share your feelings with trusted friends, family, or counselors. You're not alone in your
                            struggles.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>🧘 Practice Mindfulness</h3>
                        <p>Try meditation, deep breathing, or yoga to reduce stress and improve mental clarity.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>📅 Manage Time Wisely</h3>
                        <p>Create realistic schedules, break tasks into smaller steps, and avoid procrastination.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>🎯 Set Boundaries</h3>
                        <p>Learn to say no to excessive commitments. Balance academics with self-care and leisure.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>🤝 Build Support Networks</h3>
                        <p>Join clubs, study groups, or support groups to connect with people who share your interests
                            and encourage you to build positive relationships and support.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card">
                        <h3>💚 Seek Professional Help</h3>
                        <p>Don't hesitate to use campus counseling services or mental health hotlines when needed.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Warning Section -->
        <div class="warning-box">
            <div class="warning-icon">⚠️</div>
            <div class="warning-content">
                <h3>When to Seek Immediate Help</h3>
                <p>If you or someone you know is experiencing thoughts of self-harm, suicide, severe depression, or any
                    mental health crisis, please reach out immediately to:</p>
                <ul style="margin-top: 15px;">
                    <li><strong>Emergency Services:</strong> Call 112 (national emergency number for police, fire, and
                        ambulance)</li>
                    <li><strong>National Suicide Prevention Lifeline:</strong> Tele Manas: +91 1-800 891 4416, I
                        Call:9152987821</li>
                    <li><strong>Campus Counseling Center:</strong> Contact your school's mental health services</li>
                    <li><strong>Crisis Text Line:</strong> Text "HELLO" to 741741</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Resources Section -->
        <div class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <span class="section-icon">🔗</span>
                <h2>Helpful Resources</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <p>Here are some valuable resources for student health and wellness:</p>
                <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                    <a href="https://www.who.int/health-topics/mental-health" target="_blank" class="resource-link">WHO
                        Mental Health</a>
                    <a href="https://www.unicef.org/india/topics/mental-health" target="_blank"
                        class="resource-link">UNICEF</a>
                    <a href="https://ntf.education.gov.in/student-support-resources/" target="_blank"
                        class="resource-link">National Task Force</a>
                    <a href="https://www.mhfaindia.com/individuals/student-faculty" target="_blank"
                        class="resource-link">MHFA</a>
                    <a href="https://manodarpan.education.gov.in/" target="_blank" class="resource-link">MANODARPAN</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Action Steps Section -->
        <div class="section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <h2>Take Action Today</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="section-content">
                <img draggable="FALSE" src="/assets/r3.png" class="r3">
                <div>
                    <p>Small steps can make a big difference in your health and well-being. Here's what you can do
                        today:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Schedule a check-up with your campus health center</li>
                        <li>Download a meditation or sleep tracking app</li>
                        <li>Plan healthy meals for the week</li>
                        <li>Join a sports club or fitness class</li>
                        <li>Reach out to a friend you haven't talked to in a while</li>
                        <li>Create a realistic study schedule that includes breaks</li>
                        <li>Set a consistent sleep schedule starting tonight</li>
                        <li>Write down three things you're grateful for</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p style="margin-top: 20px;"><strong>Remember:</strong> Your health is your most valuable asset.
                        Investing in it now will benefit you for years to come.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

